'''''Combretocarpus''''' is a [[monotypic]] genus of tree in the [[Anisophylleaceae]] family. The generic name ''{{lang|el|combretocarpus}}'' is from the [[Greek language|Greek]], referring to the resemblance of its fruit to that of the genus ''[[Combretum]]''.<ref name=TFSS/> {{As of|2014|April}} ''[[The Plant List]]'' recognises the single species '''''Combretocarpus rotundatus'''''.<ref name=TPL2/>

==Description==
''Combretocarpus rotundatus'' grows as a tree up to {{convert|40|m|-1}} tall with a trunk diameter of up to {{convert|1|m|-1}}. The fissured bark is grey-brown to brown. The bisexual flowers are yellow. The fruits have three or four wings and measure up to {{convert|3|cm|in|0|abbr=on}} long. The hard heavy wood is used in heavy construction and for indoor floors and panels.<ref name=TFSS/>

==Distribution and habitat==
''Combretocarpus rotundatus'' grows naturally in [[Sumatra]], [[Peninsular Malaysia]] and [[Borneo]]. Its habitat is swamp and [[kerangas]] forests.<ref name=TFSS/>

